
Each message in the database contains several attributes:

 - id: A unique ID assigned to each message
 - message: The actual message as presented by Git
 - description: A short description explaining the message
 - action: Which action the user can or should take


                             Message IDs
                            -------------

Each message is assigned an unique ID. It starts with the prefix 'git-'
and is followed by a four digit number. The first digit indicates the
message type (debug, info, warning, error, fatal). All following digits
can be freely chosen.
